## Implementation Details

According to the official Vercel documentation fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart:

**For React applications:**
> Import from `@vercel/speed-insights/react` and include the component in your main App file.

This project correctly implements this by:
1. Using the React-specific import: `@vercel/speed-insights/react`
2. Rendering the `<SpeedInsights />` component in the main entry point (`src/main.tsx`)
3. Placing it at the root level alongside other global components

## Next Steps (for project deployment)

While the code is fully configured, to enable Speed Insights data collection on Vercel:

1. **Enable Speed Insights in Vercel Dashboard:**
   - Navigate to the Vercel dashboard
   - Select "Speed Insights" from the sidebar
   - Choose this project
   - Click "Enable"

2. **Deploy the application:**
   - Speed Insights will automatically start collecting data after deployment
   - Metrics will be available in the Vercel dashboard's Speed Insights section

